    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note><note>Il <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                                <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arechi II</persName>
                                offre al monastero di S. Sofia di <placeName key="#Cities"
                                    ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName>
                            </note>(prosegue l'elenco iniziato con il doc. 3535):</note></ab> <ab>(…) [66] Seu et ipsa <geogName ref="#estates/3415" key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property"><rs
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >curte nostra</rs> in <placeName ref="#places/2377"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Villages/settlements #Mountains #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Iron #Fiscal_property"
                                >Prata</placeName>, in loco ubi Pazzano dicitur</geogName>, cum ipsa
                            <orgName key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Quarries #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3434"><rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> Sancti
                            Petri</orgName> et ipso <rs key="#Mountains">monte</rs> cum ipso <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">plano</rs> et ipsa <rs key="#Quarries"
                            >ferrara</rs>, hęc omnia <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/85">Sancte Sophie</orgName> concessimus
                        possidendum. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p><emph>Editions</emph>: IS1 VIII, col. 581D; IS2 VIII, coll. 32D-33A; IS2 X-2,
                    col. 428D; Borgia 1769, I, p. 305; Cappelletti 1845, pp. 44-45; CSS, I, 1 [66],
                    pp. 334-335 (source of the text reproduced here). <emph>Document
                        summaries</emph>: Di Meo 1795-1819, III, p. 97; Bertolini O, 1926, 72; RIM,
                    460.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
